        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 19 at 4:54PM EDT until June 19 at 5:15PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 454 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 8 miles north of
Mocksville, or 4 miles southeast of Courtney, moving east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to trees and power lines.

Locations impacted include...
Farmington.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.

Continuous cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Move indoors immediately. Lightning is one of nature's leading
killers. Remember, if you can hear thunder, you are close enough to
be struck by lightning.

Torrential rainfall is occurring with this storm, and may lead to
flash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
